gui_open_cell_view(25.10)                            gui_open_cell_view(25.10)

Name
       gui_open_cell_view - Opens the Cell Viewer

Syntax
       gui_open_cell_view [-help]

       Opens  the  Cell  Viewer.  The Cell Viewer provides a convenient way to
       view the content of a cell, cell view, or partition without  having  to
       zoom  into  the  design.  It provides an artwork window for viewing the
       following objects:

              * any LEF library cell

              * any via cell

              * any OpenAccess database cell view

              * abstract view of any partition in the design

              * power grid view

       You can use the gui_open_cell_view command at any stage of  the  design
       flow.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the gui_open_cell_view command.

              For  a detailed description of the command, use the man command:
              man gui_open_cell_view.

Related Information
              * gui_close_cell_view

              * Tools Menu chapter of the Menu Reference

                * Cell Viewer

